One is the World's Greatest Detective with unlimited resources for his vigilante quest for justice. The other is a soldier; a black-ops killer who does whatever it takes for the greater good. What happens when the two meet? We'll never know... because Michael Cray, code-named Deathblow, is dead.

WildStorm Productions presents one of the most unusual crossovers ever in this collection of the 3-issue miniseries written by Brian Azzarello (100 BULLETS, HELLBLAZER), with stunning, evocative art by Lee Bermejo (SUPERMAN/GEN13), Tim Bradstreet (HELLBLAZER covers) & Mick Gray (PROMETHEA). The Dark Knight faces the daunting task of finishing a job that someone else started but — for reasons that remain a mystery — refused to finish. That someone was Michael Cray.

This is a mystery that spans a decade — a tale of secret agents, double agents and a charismatic madman with a fiery, lethal touch. It's also the story of two very different kinds of heroes, and the explosive results of the two crossing paths... even if one of them is dead!

description:
Madbomb riots in Manhattan! The Serpent Squad!

Steve Rogers losing faith in himself!

Captain America and Sharon continue their fight against the Serpent Squad. Cap briefly distracs them, allowing Sharon to evacuate the hostages. Sharon runs out of amo, but manages to spray Eel with a fire extinguisher. After a short fight, Cap and Sharon defeat the Serpent Squad. Cap tells Sharon to secure the Madbomb and request a pick for the Serpent Squad while he goes to stop the riot.

Standing on a truck, Cap begs the rioters to stop but he reverts in front of the mob. The mad citizens attack Cap, believing him to be an impostor, but Falcon rescues him. Falcon says that the mob could have torn him apart and Cap replies that he would not have been able to stop them.

Later, Queen Hydra watches the news about the riot alongside Mr. Fitzgerald, a bank manager. The news reveals that Nationfirst Bank, the bank attacked by the Serpent Squad, harbored a series of fradulent stock trades Nationfirst was trying to cover up. The state's attorney has frozen the bank's assets, pending further investigation.

Mr. Fitzgerald, a rival of Nationfirst, hopes to merge his interests with those of Queen Hydra, who wants to meet Fitzgerald's friends at the news.

At S.H.I.E.L.D., Sharon recieves news from Falcon that he has taken the still-skinny Cap to Iron Man so he can have a few tests. Sharon goes to a secluded cell, which contains King Cobra. Sharon begins attacking Cobra and demands to know what did they do to Cap, and Cobra replies that the Serpent Squad was fooled too. He says that they were supposed to be only a distraction.

Meanwhile, the Raft is attacked by HYDRA soldiers while Baron Zemo breaks Codename Bravo out of confinement. As Bravo and Zemo escape in a ship, the HYDRA soldiers are defeated by the Raft's security guards.

At the Quincarrier, Sharon grabs the tape that contains Machinesmith and orders the Quincarrier's computer to deactivate all communication networks. She also orders the computer to activate the self-destruct system if she doesn't reauthorize at 0800 hours. She connects the tape to the computer, awakening Machinesmith.

To be continued...
